Casablanca,yG-lKxPb5yU,UgzTmq7paTmvUvqwZiF4AaABAg,,@jackrice2770,"I see a few film students have been assigned this film. They should note a couple of important things: 

1) Note there isn't any 'filler', not one unnecessary scene. 

2) Instead of the modern film style with naked, sweaty bodies flopping around for several minutes, here we see symbols and subtle shots that tell us that yes, Ilsa and Rick ""do it"" but we're spared the pace-killing soft-core porn so prevalent today. (That shot of the searchlight when the camera cuts away). Yes, Bogie and Ilsa are wearing clothes in the next shot, but apparently folks in the '40s were a bit quicker on the uptake than today. 

3) The script is tight, and although at least three writers worked on it, the final result works perfectly. The sign of a director in complete control of his project.

4) The shadows and camera angles are works of genius. Lighting designers and cinematographers should watch it frame by frame.",2025-11-25T01:25:56Z,2025-11-25T01:25:56Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:24.745975
Casablanca,yG-lKxPb5yU,UgyPrr3qraT9RZP30sZ4AaABAg,,@jackrice2770,"Yes, in case you're a young'un, this movie has been voted one of the best by any number of film associations, One historical note: Renault says to Strasser that ""he was with the Americans when they blundered into Berlin in 1918."" Germany was never invaded during the First World War, and certainly no foreign troops, American or otherwise, entered the capital. Of course, one shouldn't rely on films for historical facts (actually, almost all 'historical' films are grossly inaccurate).

Here's looking at you, Kid.",2025-11-25T00:43:16Z,2025-11-25T00:43:16Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:24.745980
Casablanca,yG-lKxPb5yU,UgyCaNAfcFdV3oWLWJB4AaABAg,,@timothydavis1885,"There have been few movies that have equaled the romantic twists, the suspense, the drama, the musical soundtrack, as Casablanca.   As Time Goes By will go down in cinematic history as one of the greatest musical masterpieces of all time.   This was undoubtedly Humphrey Bogart's greatest work. Humphrey Bogart was unquestionably one of the greatest actors ever to grace movie screen.  Ingrid Bergman will forever be one of the most beautiful woman ever to cross Hollywood, whose theatrical performance in Casablanca seemed as though she were living out her own life, which just happened to be portrayed in this timeless work of cinematic art.   Paul Heinreid was the ultimate patriot, a part he played so well, it would go down as one of the most realistic performances ever.  This movie is without doubt one of the top 10 movies Hollywood ever produced.",2025-11-18T03:12:57Z,2025-11-18T03:12:57Z,2,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:24.745985
