Casablanca,YvVMlidSQpI,Ugynb2BeQrB7vT8dzcR4AaABAg,,@frbillnich,"Just recently came across this video.  So I am a bit of a ""come lately"" here.  However, ""Casablanca"" is my all time favorite movie.  So I want to add a comment.

For me, one of the best ""actions-speak-louder-than-words"" moments of character development is at the conclusion of the ""Knock on Wood"" musical number (during which Rick hides the letters in Sam's piano, Ferrari enters the Cafe and makes knowing (to Rick's stoic) eye contact with Rick).  

At the conclusion of the song, as the audience applauds, Sam smiles to the audience, stands and bows . . .  to RICK.

A great gesture that indicates that Sam is more than just an employee.  Later you get to see he is also a close friend, who shares a percentage in the Cafe's profits.  Maybe, like Rick, perhaps with Rick, he also has a past as a freedom fighter.",2026-01-20T17:44:29Z,2026-01-20T17:45:09Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:28.023263
