Casablanca,YvVMlidSQpI,Ugwgfuk2ZUlCyyNkUNR4AaABAg,,@solracer66,"The point that Rick rejoins the fight in the film lasts all of a second or two, yet without it the film would have been nowhere near as powerful. The shot happens right after Victor Lazlo commands the band to play La Marseillaise and the band members quickly glance at Rick who then nods his permission. That made the scene and the movie much more powerful than if the band had followed Lazlo's instructions without asking Rick whether it was ok or not. This shows that even a quick shot that's gone in an instant can be as important to the story as any other longer exposition.",2025-02-27T00:51:13Z,2025-02-27T00:51:13Z,3,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:28.023344
