Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwrEXCnBfUuus01vk14AaABAg,,@steelers6titles,"Note that Renault is a double-crosser until the end; he phones Strasser instead of the airport, to warn him of the impending escape.  He has a history of corruption,  which includes bribery and offering escape for sex.  Rick, despite his professed cynicism, in reality hates dishonesty and corruption.  Yet he seemingly trusts Renault at the end, which, given the latter's history, is somewhat mystifying.  Rick is no fool.  But the ending fits the film.  We'll never know if the partnership succeeded.",2026-05-02T17:12:38Z,2026-05-02T17:13:50Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:32.019070
