Rabat,Xcc6VMuROx0,UgzPBFM69UOiysCRK0B4AaABAg,,@lilzen202,"i´m moroccan/swedish.. born in sweden, but i was im morocco in my family home alot as a small child. I remember having a pet eagle that me and my father brought from the black market in the desert that we tamed and it would eat the nearby cats that would jump in and try and eat it, it was great haha. Fun times... My family live in a big house and i´m blessed, they would give away free finished houses a long time ago to men who fought in the world war 2, like my grandfather did against germany for french, my grandfather told me that he was shot in the foot and had to play dead when the germans came and finished off the ones that was alive.. he held his breath for minutes and played dead. He left that place alive with 4 toes :) He also brought a german mine with him and kept it as a trophy in our home. He is dead now and so is my arabic grandmother... but i still visit at times and everything just comes back.... i feel at home. Morocco is a wonderful place with wonderful, warm blooded, funny and kind people :) I also remember getting my circumcision at the age of 4 at my cousins place couse my father was to cheap to get a real doctor in the hospital, but after that was done and i screamed in agony, i remember riding a camel out on the street and having everyone nearby celebrating. Was like a circus, totally wild... never seen or experienced anything like it.... Was like a fever dream. This is normal for moroccan people btw, really cool place to visit if you want to have fun, but be careful of the taxi drivers.... and so on. They will drive you away and steal all your money even if ur arabic, but especially women.. happened to my aunt... There are thiefs and so on, so don´t get to comfortable. Friendly tip :) If your gonna walk at night time, make sure you bring your man and so on. I wouldn´t even walk alone in morocco at night or let alone drive a taxi. People will also try to scam you, so always hassle with them, and remember everything is fake here.. so if you come here as tourist go very low on the price... it costs them next to nothing couse they buy those stuff in bulk for dirt cheap, and be careful eating street food, some will make you sick for a whole week, just like the tap water will. So always boil it then cool it down in the fridge or buy it in bottles from the store. Make sure you drive the red old small taxis, and not the white or more fancier new ones.. they charge like 5x more, even more then in a european country, and you have to pay them before you leave or u are in big trouble. ´´Small Red Taxis´´ only !! remember, that is best price, even if the seatbelts might not work :) The taxi driver are most likely going to be extremely friendly and funny and also fair, since you can see the taxi meter.",2025-04-30T00:42:22Z,2025-04-30T00:42:22Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:01:39.683555
