Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDXfrhFZHe,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@Roathcourt,@ thank you so much Angela,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,0,True,,2026-05-10T02:01:51.185824
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg.AGx6eqm664_AGx71udc2kW,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We loved our time in Morocco! We especially enjoyed Fes, but we spent a month between Marrakech, the Sahara Desert, and Fes. We would definitely like to spend time exploring more of the country. —Judy",2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,0,True,,2026-05-10T02:01:51.292751
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg.AGsAZLPMU1UAGsBwyFqJ6j,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Syed, You will always be at the mercy of the border agent who you talk to. Offhand, I don't recall that they asked us anything. We may have had to show proof of onward travel afterwards and possibly the address of our riad where we were staying, but nothing else. These are common questions we get asked occasionally, but I think every agent does their own thing. It can also be dependent on your passport, and we are Americans. That's not to say in these unusual times that border agents will continue to be as kind to us. —Judy",2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-10T02:01:51.414773
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYDb2MBC3R,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Thelminetta, Neither of us recalls that we had to do that. Of course, you're always at the mercy of the specific passport security personnel you end up getting and possibly also your passport. You might enjoy our other episodes from our 40+ days in Morocco. —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-04-05T17:42:27Z,2025-04-05T17:42:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-10T02:01:51.506596
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYH2U3AXCU,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@thelminettas8694,"Thank you! I find your vlogs very informative. I avoid those that don’t teach - how to get to and from a destination, best location for accomodation, transportation, etc. My husband and I started traveling more and thought Marrakech and Fes are interesting cities to explore after Portugal and Spain in the fall. Thank you! I’m a subscriber now.",2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,1,True,,2026-05-10T02:01:51.506612
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYhQuTvl7z,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We are so flattered. Thank you very much! You are right about Morocco being a perfect complement to those countries. We've been to Madrid and Barcelona, but people mentioned that Granada is a great place to visit before or after Morocco because there are certain similarities. After the Moors were expelled from Spain, many of them settled in Marrakech. Likewise certain North African dynasties once ruled parts of Spain, including Granada. We hope you have a great time! —Judy",2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-10T02:01:51.506617
