Tangier,ChzAHZs9JyQ,UgymJFbtaqCCa9Chgul4AaABAg,,@Philly-Morocco,"I usually don’t comment on videos, but I honestly felt I had to say something here because the information you shared is not accurate. Before making claims about Moroccan heritage, it’s important to do proper research.

Zellige, carved woodwork, jibs/plaster craftsmanship, and Moroccan architecture in general are not just “Arab” or generic “Islamic” styles. They are part of a deep Moroccan artistic tradition with its own history, identity, and influence, going back long before Moroccan culture spread into Andalusia. The same goes for pastilla, which is a Moroccan dish.

Morocco has its own architecture, design, craftsmanship, and artistic identity. I respect your platform, but I hope you correct this and avoid spreading misinformation to your audience.",2026-05-08T15:50:47Z,2026-05-08T15:50:47Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:02:15.025942
