Tourism,ET9-7Ooh3O8,UgzPjjFSDr-FepBHCkJ4AaABAg,,@JamesColeslaws,"i never got the idea of americans complaining about inflation or something being too expensive...that first bread the meat alone would be like 50euros where im from hence they dont serve stuff like that where im from..plus its also MASSIVE like actually Massive, i wouldnt even mind paying 30 dollars for that sized bread filled with meat that we cant even serve here coz its a delicacy especially in that size...the salaries there are also really good due to the outdated taxing system so they dont take like 60 to 80% of what you make well depends how much you got but still, Even a uber driver there could make pretty good money if he worked long hours and lets say like 5 to 7 days a week",2026-05-10T01:15:47Z,2026-05-10T01:15:47Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:02:18.348764
