Tourism,ET9-7Ooh3O8,Ugxl5913lEet67tyuAV4AaABAg,,@drock9083,"OK this an honest story. Back in high school, I mean WAY back a few friends and myself would drive 60 miles to L.A. (a lot less traffic, buck a gallon gas) to try various ""famous"" L.A. eateries. The time we went to Pink's we had the usual menu suspects and it was just fine. I noticed that the menu did not have a 'Mexican hot dog' featured (hot dog and cheese wrapped in a flour or corn tort) which was something I'd been eating since I was a kid. The cooks were of course hispanic and since I spoke spanish I asked them why they did'nt make a Mexican hot dog. they just shrugged their shoulders. On our next visit a few weeks later sure enough, there was a mexican hot dog on the menu and it was pretty good.",2026-05-10T01:11:03Z,2026-05-10T01:16:24Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:02:18.348784
