Tourism,O8cuIxngLqI,UgxIqHj1mCwO4wRcbjJ4AaABAg,,@Seizo-g8i,"Yeah - taking photos of people anywhere without their permission is bad everywhere. And, trains are not quiet zones in Japan - at rush hour, people are often alone, so they do not talk to strangers. But, at other times, when people are in groups or pairs, they talk and it is not necessarily quiet. And , like in other no-tipping cultures in the world (2/3 of the world!), it is great. No worries - just pay for the food and leave.",2026-02-18T00:54:44Z,2026-02-18T00:54:44Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:02:20.394790
