Tourism,O8cuIxngLqI,UgytS51-523xVSqNuu54AaABAg,,@Bminutes,"The tipping one will be so hard for me if I ever go. In the US, tipping is very much expected and it's rude not to. I live in Vegas which is a service industry town, so I tip VERY well. I went to the Philippines where they're kind of neutral on tipping. Like, they will be thankful if you do, but it's not expected and I still had the urge to make sure I tip well.

I have heard the tipping thing in Japan is also changing in recent years, that it's rare for anyone to get offended by it, but it's still not expected.",2026-01-30T03:53:18Z,2026-01-30T03:53:18Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:02:20.394824
