AFCON,CdWcGc47Rv8,UgzcQMbX50Z3YR9SVXN4AaABAg,,@Slixis_3,"“IF A TEAM LEAVES THE FIELD” refers to the situation where the team, as a collective entity, leaves the field of play. In the present case, however, several players remained on the pitch. At most, this was only a partial departure by some players. Therefore, the automatic application of the article is not justified. It is a misreading of the text, arbitrary and unfair. THIS IS NOT LAW.
Had the referee definitively stopped the match, invoking Article 82 to award the championship title to one of the teams would have been legitimate. But the match continued. The victory was officially validated on paper. Law 5 of the International Football Association Board (IFAB), a fundamental principle of football law, states that the referee’s decisions regarding facts connected with play are final and irreversible. That simply settles the matter. Senegal retains the title. Any other decision would be contrary to morality.",2026-03-19T17:09:28Z,2026-03-19T17:09:28Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:02:47.249662
