Tourisme,tQG5jBBGn2Q,Ugwfm0a3qB18GKYq-Gl4AaABAg,,@mmmikeyyy,"Hey Callum, thanks for the video. Excellent work. I find the resilience of the Afrikaners quite admirable. I wonder how they manage to secure a large area such as Orania. It's a huge perimeter to secure. Anyway, I too would find life in SA exhausting. For a different experience of Africa, I'd recommend The Shadow of the Sun, a book written by Ryszard Kapuściński (originally in Polish). I read the French translation (titled Ébène) about 20 years ago and it left a lasting impression. One story it tells concerns a giant muddy pothole in which vehicles inescapably get caught, from which they can only be extracted with hired labor over a period of time. The pothole is never repaired to preserve the economic activity that has developed around it. People make money pulling vehicles through the mud, street vendors sell food, refreshments, etc. The sinkhole you showed reminded me of that story. The tone of the English translation is supposed to differ from that of the French translation. The French version is memorable, and if the English one is even half as good, it should be worth a read.",2026-05-08T04:28:09Z,2026-05-08T04:28:09Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-10T02:03:21.813493
